was once naive like you.

44:10.543 --> 44:11.743
- So what changed ya?

44:14.943 --> 44:16.743
- If I had to pinpoint it on one thing,

44:16.744 --> 44:19.510
I'd say it was the war.

44:19.511 --> 44:22.812
I came home and my marriage
quickly fell apart.

44:24.044 --> 44:26.479
I bought a cabin by the lake,

44:27.579 --> 44:30.812
took up carving, I tried
to forget those images

44:30.813 --> 44:33.146
that were burned in my brain.

44:34.814 --> 44:38.146
I used to think God was
this all-powerful being

44:38.147 --> 44:42.916
who looked after us,
but now I know better.

44:44.081 --> 44:47.515
The only one who's looking
after you, Michael, is you.

44:49.917 --> 44:52.182
- It's a pretty sad outlook on life.

44:52.183 --> 44:55.283
- It's just the truth.

44:55.284 --> 44:56.650
- Not for me, it isn't.

44:56.651 --> 44:57.917
- Oh, yeah?

44:57.918 --> 44:59.883
And what makes you so special?

44:59.884 --> 45:01.818
- I'm not saying I'm special.

45:01.819 --> 45:05.851
My life is no more or less
amazing than anybody else's,

45:05.852 --> 45:10.853
but everywhere I look, I
can see God's handiwork.

45:11.519 --> 45:12.952
In everything.

45:12.953 --> 45:14.886
- You know what they call that, Michael?

45:14.887 --> 45:18.553
They call that "confirmation bias."

45:18.554 --> 45:20.454
You see anything that you want to see,

45:20.455 --> 45:22.654
and when it does not
fit in your little box,

45:22.655 --> 45:24.487
you reject it.

45:24.488 --> 45:25.788
- I know what you're gettin' at, okay?

45:25.789 --> 45:28.721
Yes, humans are pattern-seekers
who see shapes in clouds

45:28.722 --> 45:31.189
and Jesus' face in potato chips.

45:31.190 --> 45:35.122
That's fine, but,

45:35.123 --> 45:37.323
haven't you ever had something

45:37.324 --> 45:40.623
happen to you where you knew that it had

45:40.624 --> 45:41.890
nothing to do with chance.

45:41.891 --> 45:44.758
That it had something to do with

45:44.759 --> 45:47.559
something greater than you?

45:48.725 --> 45:50.859
- In the world of random chance,

45:50.860 --> 45:52.892
things are bound to happen.

45:52.893 --> 45:54.358
- So nothing then?

45:54.359 --> 45:55.626
- Nothing what?

45:55.627 --> 45:57.561
- Nothing greater than you?

46:00.060 --> 46:01.861
- When we get out of this place,

46:01.862 --> 46:04.427
you're comin' with me up to my cabin,

46:04.428 --> 46:05.727
and after we catch our dinner,

46:05.728 --> 46:08.295
we're gonna carve away
on a couple of blocks

46:08.296 --> 46:13.062
as the sun sets on the
waters smooth as glass,

46:13.063 --> 46:16.062
and when the last rays of
sunlight hits your face,

46:16.063 --> 46:19.163
you're gonna get the
calls of a thousand voices

46:19.164 --> 46:22.697
that maybe you forgot shared

46:22.698 --> 46:26.097
this random, chaotic, painful,

46:26.098 --> 46:28.866
beautiful world with us.

46:32.066 --> 46:33.965
- Sounds good.

46:33.966 --> 46:35.632
- Then it's set then?

46:35.633 --> 46:36.633
- It's set.

46:36.634 --> 46:38.567
- You're gonna have to give
me a couple of weeks, though.

46:38.568 --> 46:41.266
I've been in this place too stinkin' long

46:41.267 --> 46:44.100
and who knows what it looks like now.

46:49.169 --> 46:51.202
- Gah, this
game does not agree with me.

46:51.203 --> 46:53.335
- No, it doesn't.

46:53.336 --> 46:55.470
- Can we pick up on it later?

46:55.471 --> 46:57.136
- Yeah.

46:57.137 --> 47:01.270
- Ya know, Michael,

47:01.271 --> 47:02.504
science does have a answer

47:02.505 --> 47:06.437
to how we live in such
a finely-tuned universe.

47:06.438 --> 47:08.205
You ever heard of quantum mechanics?

47:08.206 --> 47:09.538
- I've heard of it.
- Yeah.

47:09.539 --> 47:12.271
It predicts an infinite
number of universes

47:12.272 --> 47:14.940
with different properties in each one.

47:14.941 --> 47:17.841
Most are empty of life.

47:19.074 --> 47:21.006
This one works.

47:21.007 --> 47:23.607
So, maybe there's an alternate universe

47:23.608 --> 47:27.909
where you and I are playing
Yahtzee cancer-free.

47:27.943 --> 47:31.076
- And I whip your butt every game.

47:36.076 --> 47:38.210
- An infinite number of universes

47:38.211 --> 47:41.443
with an infinite number of possibilities

47:41.444 --> 47:44.512
and you're saying there's no room for God?

47:48.947 --> 47:52.580
- There is no miracle, son, I'm sorry.

47:53.880 --> 47:56.513
I wish I was wrong about that,

47:56.514 --> 47:58.580
but I'm not.

48:21.451 --> 48:22.451
- Hey, guys.

48:22.452 --> 48:24.016
- Hey, Dr. McAlpine.

48:24.017 --> 48:25.918
- Well, I thought I was comin' in here

48:25.919 --> 48:28.218
today to give you guys some bad news,

48:28.219 --> 48:29.585
to tell you that the second round

48:29.586 --> 48:31.386
of chemotherapy had failed,

48:31.420 --> 48:34.386
but, actually, it is pretty remarkable.

48:34.420 --> 48:37.086
I've never seen anything
like this in my career.

48:37.087 --> 48:39.854
Yesterday, your blast cells were at 80%

48:39.855 --> 48:42.086
and today, this morning's tests,

48:42.087 --> 48:44.222
and I double-checked these tests.

48:45.988 --> 48:48.322
You're in complete remission.

48:49.556 --> 48:52.388
Now, there's a pretty
good chance of relapse,

48:52.389 --> 48:56.256
so we need to start planning
for a bone marrow transplant.

48:56.257 --> 48:57.890
That planning means we need to find

48:57.891 --> 49:00.657
the best possible match for Michael,

49:00.658 --> 49:05.558
but for right now, get outta here.

49:06.625 --> 49:09.024
You can go home.

50:17.704 --> 50:21.504
- I cannot wait to go on
a proper date with you.

50:21.505 --> 50:23.203
We can go to the movie theater

50:23.204 --> 50:26.004
and we can buy one of those
really big buckets of popcorn

50:26.005 --> 50:29.204
and just drench it in butter,
and buy all the candy...

50:29.205 --> 50:30.873
- That's such a good idea,

50:30.874 --> 50:32.906
because nothing says, "I just beat cancer"

50:32.907 --> 50:34.539
than going into cardiac arrest.

50:34.540 --> 50:37.974
- Hey, you can bring Sheila,
we could make it a double-date.

50:37.975 --> 50:40.875
- No, no, no, I don't
wanna intrude, you guys go.

50:42.441 --> 50:44.208
- What's wrong?

50:45.442 --> 50:48.810
- Do you guys wanna do
something really cool?

51:15.146 --> 51:17.145
- Hi, I'm Michelle.
- Tony,

51:17.146 --> 51:19.146
it's nice to meet you.

51:19.147 --> 51:20.514
- Michael.
- Yeah, hi.

51:20.515 --> 51:22.113
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice meeting you.

51:22.114 --> 51:23.347
- I just wanna say it's really great

51:23.348 --> 51:25.581
what you're doing for my
dad, I'm really happy,

51:25.582 --> 51:26.582
this is awesome.

51:26.582 --> 51:27.582
- You wanna get started?

51:27.583 --> 51:29.314
- Yeah, hang on just a second.

51:29.315 --> 51:30.816
- Alright, guys, come on out.

51:49.386 --> 51:54.119
♫ Hey, I'm dreamin' again

51:55.487 --> 52:00.487
♫ It's just like you to
see everything I want to be

52:02.989 --> 52:07.856
♫ I am awake at last

52:09.456 --> 52:11.889
♫ I see my path

52:11.890 --> 52:16.189
♫ waitin' right in front of me

52:16.190 --> 52:19.323
♫ For

52:19.324 --> 52:23.123
♫ you to

52:23.124 --> 52:25.925
♫ Make what you make of it

52:25.926 --> 52:29.424
♫ as the morning light breaks

52:29.425 --> 52:32.259
♫ You gotta live your life

52:32.260 --> 52:36.793
♫ like there's no tomorrow

52:36.794 --> 52:40.593
♫ Make what you make of it

52:40.594 --> 52:44.160
♫ to light the fire, oh so beautiful

52:44.161 --> 52:45.561
♫ Make through the day

52:45.562 --> 52:50.563
♫ just like there's no tomorrow

52:53.129 --> 52:55.297
♫ Wonderful day

53:05.532 --> 53:08.298
- Today was a good day.

53:08.299 --> 53:10.165
- I agree.

53:38.037 --> 53:41.404
- Dr. McAlpine, he said
I'd probably relapse.

53:43.205 --> 53:46.638
- I just really, really thought
that it was gone for good.

53:46.639 --> 53:48.305
- Me too.

53:53.773 --> 53:56.473
- God gave us that miracle
and then, it's like,

53:56.474 --> 53:58.707
he just took it away.

54:00.374 --> 54:03.475
I just don't understand what He's doing.

54:05.074 --> 54:08.975
I mean, all the people in that hospital,

54:08.976 --> 54:11.775
all of the children, Annalisa, why?

54:11.776 --> 54:13.342
Why can't He just save everyone?

54:13.343 --> 54:14.409
- I don't know.
- Why?

54:14.410 --> 54:16.576
Isn't that what you would do?

54:16.577 --> 54:18.645
I just don't get it.

54:20.945 --> 54:22.244
- Come here.

54:25.112 --> 54:26.913
Let me show you something.

54:27.879 --> 54:29.978
You see that right there?

54:29.979 --> 54:31.879
- What am I looking at?

54:31.880 --> 54:33.546
- This.

54:33.547 --> 54:37.381
This little paint chip
is our time on Earth.

54:38.915 --> 54:43.181
And all this paint, all of it,

54:55.584 --> 54:57.317
is eternity.

54:58.918 --> 55:00.817
- What does that mean?

55:00.818 --> 55:03.984
- Our time on Earth is a blink

55:03.985 --> 55:06.051
to the rest of it.

55:07.553 --> 55:10.218
Death isn't the end of my journey.

55:10.219 --> 55:12.452
- Don't say death, Michael,
please don't say death.

55:12.453 --> 55:14.052
You're not gonna die, okay?

55:14.053 --> 55:19.053
- I'm not sayin' that, I'm
not, it's just perspective.

55:19.054 --> 55:22.353
That gives me peace.

55:22.354 --> 55:25.088
I don't want to be afraid
through all of this.

55:27.322 --> 55:30.957
- I understand that completely.

55:32.823 --> 55:37.490
Can we just try to stay positive, please?

55:37.491 --> 55:39.890
I know that the bone marrow
transplant is going to work,

55:39.891 --> 55:42.491
I know it is, so we don't have to have all

55:42.492 --> 55:44.925
these eternity talks, okay?

55:44.926 --> 55:46.425
- Yeah.

55:54.894 --> 55:57.494
I've got somethin' worth fighting for.

56:09.229 --> 56:10.596
What?

56:11.496 --> 56:14.596
- Stupid, stupid pigmobile.

56:14.597 --> 56:17.629
Why'd you have to use the pigmobile?

56:17.630 --> 56:18.998
Couldn't you have used, like,

56:19.032 --> 56:21.565
the stars in the sky or something?

56:25.033 --> 56:27.331
- Yeah, that probably
would have been better.

56:27.332 --> 56:28.831
- Because I see this one up there

56:28.832 --> 56:32.332
and it's a hunter with a bow.

56:32.333 --> 56:33.699
- Oh.
- Shooting

56:33.700 --> 56:35.465
an octopus.
- Yeah, you're good.

56:35.466 --> 56:37.099
That's funny.

56:37.100 --> 56:38.301
- Stop.

56:59.771 --> 57:03.103
Hey.

57:03.104 --> 57:04.971
- Hey, dude.

57:04.972 --> 57:07.572
- Whatcha doin'?

57:07.573 --> 57:09.606
- Just lookin'.

57:11.139 --> 57:12.539
- If you're lookin' for that geocache,

57:12.540 --> 57:15.306
that was further down that way.

57:15.307 --> 57:17.540
Treasure, nerd stuff.

57:22.408 --> 57:24.342
You okay?

57:27.009 --> 57:28.943
- Sheila and I broke up.

57:29.742 --> 57:30.944
- What?

57:32.610 --> 57:34.342
I'm sorry to hear that.

57:34.343 --> 57:36.477
- So, whatever.

57:39.045 --> 57:41.176
- I've got dinner at the house

57:41.177 --> 57:42.778
if you wanna come eat?

57:42.779 --> 57:45.946
- I'm alright, man, I'll come in a bit.

57:48.078 --> 57:50.879
- I feel so blessed that this,

57:50.880 --> 57:53.245
the bone marrow's comin' from you.

57:53.246 --> 57:55.047
- You just think James
is a pansy, don't you?

57:55.048 --> 57:57.580
- Total pansy, huge pansy.

57:57.581 --> 58:01.080
- Nah, man, I'm glad I could help.

58:01.081 --> 58:03.847
- See you at the house.

58:09.883 --> 58:11.883
- I need this to work, Mike.

58:15.350 --> 58:17.649
I just feel like life
keeps kicking me down

58:17.650 --> 58:19.584
and down and down and every time

58:19.585 --> 58:21.350
I try to get back up and fight it,

58:21.351 --> 58:25.185
it sweeps me under the rug.

58:28.919 --> 58:30.820
I need it to work.

58:34.520 --> 58:36.153
What are we havin'?

58:37.187 --> 58:38.554
- Ribs.

58:39.754 --> 58:41.988
Ribs, pork, whatever you want.

58:42.989 --> 58:44.555
Come on.

58:47.255 --> 58:51.255
- There he is, there he is.

58:51.256 --> 58:52.789
How you feelin'?

58:52.790 --> 58:54.456
- I feel great.

58:54.457 --> 58:56.156
- You look great, bro.

58:56.157 --> 58:58.823
Bone marrow day, bone marrow day,

58:58.824 --> 59:00.524
bone marrow day.

59:00.525 --> 59:02.525
- Hey, I have a little
present from the munchkins.

59:04.592 --> 59:05.958
- Yeah, yeah, look at that.

59:05.959 --> 59:06.960
- Can't even spell.

59:06.961 --> 59:08.625
- Alright, this is it.

59:08.626 --> 59:10.525
- There it is, right there.

59:10.526 --> 59:12.726
- Ladies and gentleman,
that is what the inside

59:12.727 --> 59:14.926
of Matt Boyum looks like, disgusting.

59:14.927 --> 59:15.993
- How does this work?

59:15.994 --> 59:17.392
You just plug it in and then it goes right

59:17.393 --> 59:18.394
into his veins?

59:18.395 --> 59:20.027
- Yep, and once it hits his blood stream,

59:20.028 --> 59:21.894
it'll start to pick up
his brother's traits.

59:21.895 --> 59:23.293
- That's right, he'll be better looking,

59:23.294 --> 59:25.261
he'll be more handsome, he'll be smarter.

59:25.262 --> 59:26.962
- Making women uncomfortable,

59:26.963 --> 59:28.328
these are things I'm looking forward to.

59:28.329 --> 59:31.128
- Ladies, Matt Boyum, here.

59:31.129 --> 59:32.796
My older brother, he
needed something from me,

59:32.797 --> 59:35.128
I gave, I stepped up,
you remember this face.

59:35.129 --> 59:36.598
- Cha-ching.

59:39.598 --> 59:41.630
- Once I finish up here,
in about 15 minutes,

59:41.631 --> 59:42.931
it'll all be in.

59:42.932 --> 59:45.398
- Matt Boyum, you're my hero.

59:52.967 --> 59:54.434
- Get the nurse.

59:58.334 --> 01:00:00.801
- Katie, Michael's burning up in there,

01:00:00.802 --> 01:00:02.001
he needs your help.

01:00:02.002 --> 01:00:03.968
- He'll get his next
dose in about 30 minutes.

01:00:03.969 --> 01:00:07.069
- No, not in 30 minutes,

01:00:07.070 --> 01:00:10.035
you're gonna help him right now.

01:00:10.036 --> 01:00:11.435
- I can get you some cold towels,

01:00:11.436 --> 01:00:13.136
but that's all I can do.

01:01:08.946 --> 01:01:11.445
- You wanna get out of here?

01:01:11.446 --> 01:01:12.646
- Hm?

01:01:14.180 --> 01:01:17.081
Are you okay, do you need something?

01:01:19.082 --> 01:01:22.580
- We were at prom,

01:01:22.581 --> 01:01:24.949
we were dancing.

01:01:29.749 --> 01:01:33.850
And then I twirled you and
you looked so beautiful.

01:01:39.117 --> 01:01:41.818
You wore that red dress.

01:01:46.185 --> 01:01:47.951
So beautiful.

01:02:47.062 --> 01:02:48.796
- Wow.

01:02:58.197 --> 01:03:00.065
Stay still.

01:03:01.665 --> 01:03:03.365
You okay?

01:03:05.198 --> 01:03:07.733
- You have to dance with me.

01:03:09.265 --> 01:03:12.132
That dress is too good to pass up.

01:04:45.949 --> 01:04:47.115
- Can I come in?

01:04:47.116 --> 01:04:48.782
- Yeah, absolutely.

01:04:48.783 --> 01:04:51.215
- You look fantastic.
- Thank you.

01:04:51.216 --> 01:04:52.882
- You look great.

01:04:52.883 --> 01:04:54.216
What day are you at?

01:04:54.217 --> 01:04:55.950
- 100.

01:04:55.951 --> 01:04:58.282
- 100?
- Yeah.

01:04:58.283 --> 01:05:00.550
- That's good, that's good.

01:05:00.551 --> 01:05:02.217
You're almost free.

01:05:02.218 --> 01:05:04.651
- Almost.
- [Mr. Fenton) You know,

01:05:04.652 --> 01:05:08.352
I want to thank you for what
you did up at the cabin.

01:05:08.386 --> 01:05:11.151
- Tony, he wasn't supposed to tell you.

01:05:11.152 --> 01:05:14.252
- I know, he was never
good at keeping secrets.

01:05:14.253 --> 01:05:15.686
- Apparently not.

01:05:15.687 --> 01:05:18.088
- I got a little surprise for you.

01:05:27.455 --> 01:05:32.155
- Wow, this is beautiful.

01:05:32.156 --> 01:05:34.389
- Oh, no, you're not converting me.

01:05:36.058 --> 01:05:38.657
I also carve unicorns and fairies.

01:05:38.658 --> 01:05:40.289
- Fairy tale stuff, right.

01:05:40.290 --> 01:05:42.891
- You're a good kid, Michael.

01:05:42.892 --> 01:05:45.290
Go conquer the world.

01:05:57.061 --> 01:05:59.226
- You're next.

01:05:59.227 --> 01:06:02.595
- Yeah, you can count on it.

01:06:14.497 --> 01:06:16.629
- Dear Heavenly Father, we are so thankful

01:06:16.630 --> 01:06:18.698
that you've healed Michael.

01:06:18.731 --> 01:06:21.463
Let his life testify to your faithfulness.

01:06:21.464 --> 01:06:23.898
You are the great Healer.

01:06:23.899 --> 01:06:26.399
In Jesus' Name we pray, Amen.

01:06:28.999 --> 01:06:32.565
- I would like to propose a toast

01:06:32.566 --> 01:06:35.332
to the bone marrow king of Minnesota,

01:06:35.333 --> 01:06:37.199
my dear brother, Matt.

01:06:37.200 --> 01:06:39.240
- Hey, that is Mr. King Bone Marrow
to you, alright?

01:06:43.602 --> 01:06:45.467
- I would like to say a prayer.

01:06:45.468 --> 01:06:47.300
- Uh, mom, dad just prayed.

01:06:47.301 --> 01:06:49.468
- Well, I would like to add something.

01:06:49.469 --> 01:06:51.770
- Matt, you need more prayer!

01:06:51.803 --> 01:06:53.236
- That I do!

01:06:53.269 --> 01:06:57.736
Thank you, Lord, for bringing
Michelle into our lives.

01:06:57.737 --> 01:07:00.804
She's a beautiful gift to this family.

01:07:00.805 --> 01:07:03.071
May you continue to bless her

01:07:03.072 --> 01:07:07.572
in everything she does, Amen.

01:07:10.106 --> 01:07:11.639
- I love you, guys.

01:07:14.507 --> 01:07:16.041
- Let's eat.

01:07:17.007 --> 01:07:18.340
Let's start with the beef.

01:07:18.341 --> 01:07:19.674
- Beef.

01:07:22.474 --> 01:07:25.876
- Don't answer your phone
at the table, that's rude.

01:07:26.842 --> 01:07:28.641
- Hi, this is Michael.

01:07:28.642 --> 01:07:29.642
- Alright.

01:07:29.643 --> 01:07:30.943
- Okay, hey.

01:07:34.543 --> 01:07:35.576
What?

01:07:46.378 --> 01:07:48.245
- Michael, who is it?

01:07:48.246 --> 01:07:50.113
- Uh, what does that mean?

01:08:03.214 --> 01:08:08.049
- Okay, thank you.

01:08:08.050 --> 01:08:10.150
- No, no, no, no, no.

01:08:11.482 --> 01:08:13.117
What'd he say?

01:08:14.417 --> 01:08:16.151
What'd he say?

01:08:17.151 --> 01:08:18.582
What did he say?

01:08:19.585 --> 01:08:21.017
- No, no, no, no.

01:08:21.018 --> 01:08:22.250
No, no.

01:08:26.752 --> 01:08:31.352
- I don't understand, you
just got out of there.

01:08:31.353 --> 01:08:33.787
You just got out of there.

01:08:36.453 --> 01:08:38.319
- Oh, honey.

01:08:41.020 --> 01:08:42.388
- Hey.

01:08:49.523 --> 01:08:51.555
I won't quit fighting.

01:08:52.555 --> 01:08:55.890
- I was really starting to
get used to this idea of, uh,

01:08:56.957 --> 01:09:01.957
this healing God that
you talk about so much.

01:09:04.892 --> 01:09:06.160
- Matt.

